<div id="review_3682127362" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3682127362" />
    <a title="Jay Wright" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/54431518-jay-wright"><img alt="Jay Wright" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1459360838p2/54431518.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3682127362?book_show_action=true">Dec 19, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jay Wright" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jay Wright" href="/user/show/54431518-jay-wright">Jay Wright</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780399230196" href="/book/show/1293573.The_Seven_Songs_of_Merlin">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3682127362" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15939655633668422453">The second in the series. Merlin is a headstrong youth who is not willing to listen to reason. He wants his mother and conjures her, but she is stricken with a curse and Merlin has one cycle of the moon to discover 7 secrets. The tasks are interesting and he has two companions. This is a good clean fantasy sory about Merlin in the early years. It is teen friendly.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


