<div id="review_3166593289" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3166593289" />
    <a title="Jacque" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8358774-jacque"><img alt="Jacque" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1574009939p2/8358774.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3166593289?book_show_action=true">Feb 02, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jacque" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jacque" href="/user/show/8358774-jacque">Jacque</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3166593289" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9191606551697760111">Such a good sequel! Merlin was pretty annoying and immature for the first 1/3 of the book, but he is only like what 12? The rest of the book he grew, matured, and learned a lot. Many secrets about him are revealed as well as a bit of a setting up for the third book. The jester was pretty annoying but eventually he grew on me a bit, but I sure hope he isn&apos;t a future sidekick for Merlin. Very excited to dive into the next book!</span>
  <span id="freeText9191606551697760111" style="display:none">Such a good sequel! Merlin was pretty annoying and immature for the first 1/3 of the book, but he is only like what 12? The rest of the book he grew, matured, and learned a lot. Many secrets about him are revealed as well as a bit of a setting up for the third book. The jester was pretty annoying but eventually he grew on me a bit, but I sure hope he isn't a future sidekick for Merlin. Very excited to dive into the next book!</span>
