  <span id="freeText13922091891170527505" style="display:none">"The Seven Songs" by T.A. Barron is set in the ancient land of Fincayra. The main character is Merlin, a wizard and other characters are Rhia, a tree like girl, Elen his mother and Bumbelwy, a jester. I found this book from reading the first of this series known as the merlin saga.<br /><br />"The Seven Songs" is about Merlin going to find the souls of seven songs in order to go to the other world which is a spirit world to help his mother get well. She is sick because he had brought her to Fincayra and when they were going to smell a flower a trap was set and made Elen very ill. On his way to find the seven songs Rhia joined him and he found a horrible jester who followed him on his journey.<br /><br />I thought how the book ending was really nice and my favorite part of the book is when Merlin finds Shim, a giant and he helps Merlin go across the lands.<br /><br />Personally I liked the book and some similar books would obviously be in the series itself and someone who might like this would be someone who enjoys fantasy books or mythology books.</span>
