              <span id="reviewTextContainer2977518712" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16575982280418584056">Hot damn does Barron know how to rush the heck out of a story. Seven lessons that need to be learned at points the span the whole island? Surely this will be an epic, drawn-out—oh it&apos;s basically just one per chapter. Wham bam Merlin does not actually learn any of these lessons ma&apos;am. Which is funny since the first one is Changing. And he doesn&apos;t. Change. Like, at all. (For 90% of the book and then right at the end he does (sort of, mainly he just admits his mistakes, I don&apos;t know if that quite c</span>
  <span id="freeText16575982280418584056" style="display:none">Hot damn does Barron know how to rush the heck out of a story. Seven lessons that need to be learned at points the span the whole island? Surely this will be an epic, drawn-out—oh it's basically just one per chapter. Wham bam Merlin does not actually learn any of these lessons ma'am. Which is funny since the first one is Changing. And he doesn't. Change. Like, at all. (For 90% of the book and then right at the end he does (sort of, mainly he just admits his mistakes, I don't know if that quite counts) because his stubbornness is no longer needed for dramatic tension but how much you wanna bet he's gonna be back to his old bullheadedness in the next one.)<br /><br />I mean, sure, his pacing does make these real page-turners, especially if you skip most of the mediocre prose. Am I being unfair here? I might be being unfair here. This is a YA book, after all, and maybe that's just how you have to write for a younger audience. Especially if you have to fill your pages with repetitive exposition and inane inner monologuing because your "plot" is only 30 pages long.<br /><br />Anyway, the next book is about standing up to bullies so maybe I'll get my comeuppance. (EDIT: I thought book 3 was the one with Dinatius, apparently I was misremembering. Woops.)<br /><br />This was a terrible idea. My childhood is dead.</span>
