<div id="review_2185722078" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2185722078" />
    <a title="Andrew C" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/70999506-andrew-c"><img alt="Andrew C" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1504648668p2/70999506.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2185722078?book_show_action=true">Jan 16, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Andrew C" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Andrew C" href="/user/show/70999506-andrew-c">Andrew C</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780142419205" href="/book/show/9705899-the-seven-songs">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2185722078" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1724140291459598110">I really liked reading this book. I learned a lot about the main characters and the wizard, Tuatha. Merlin greatly develops in this book. In the beginning, his fatal flaw is hubris. He is not humble and he is cocky. After completing the seven songs, Merlin now has humility and learns how little he really does know. Once again, this is another action packed, surprising, a creative book with magic.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


